main event: A round silver object was observed in West Palm Beach, Florida on January 28, 1955.
interesting points: The object approached from the Northeast and then proceeded south after making an orbit.,The reported size of the object was approximately 14 inches in diameter.,The sighting lasted for about 1 hour.,The object fits the description of a weather balloon based on its shape and behavior.,The observation was made by a civilian with no optics used.
